<TITLE> Satellite channel distributors to pay more duty </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 9 (bdnews24.com)  Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam Monday proposed to hike the rate of supplementary duty for satellite channel distributors to 35 percent from 15 percent now. "The proprietors or distributors of foreign TV channels are not paying the VAT applicable on commercials depriving the government from its fair share of revenue," the adviser said in his budget speech for fiscal 2008-09. Local satellite TV channels now pay 15 percent VAT on the commercials telecast, but the foreign TV channels pay no VAT on commercials. "Although these commercials are not directly targeted towards our local consumers, they indirectly help creating import demands for commodities shown on these commercials," the adviser said. bd
